                <note rend="inline" type="source">562.8F2/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-02T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 2, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. For Johnson. Your 322, May 31, 5.00 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d918fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> You are instructed to propose for inclusion in final
                    convention revision a stipulation to protect gray whale similar to that
                    contained in Section 7 of the American Whaling Act.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
